    "Let C κ be a simple cycle on vertices [κ].",
    "For each vertex ω ∈ [κ], define a layer",
    "consisting of γ vertices that represent the \"blow-up\" of the cycle node ω.",
    "The collection of all such vertices forms the cycle nodes of the graph:",
    "Between every two consecutive layers L ω and L ω+1 (with the convention L κ+1 = L 1), we insert a complete bipartite graph:"
